item.title: Help
item.dc:creator: @White_Castle White Castle
item.description:
@White_Castle wrote:

1: Don’t talk in all caps.
2: You need to set your classpaths. You could have used the search button or even google, but eh.

darkest_mage posted this:

Click Start Go up to My computer RIGHT click, and select properties. Now Click the Tab: Advanced. When you are in the proper spot you should see this window: [img]http://realmofrunescape.com/SystemProperties.gif[/img] Now, Click the Button: Environment Variables And click the top "New" button, Now Type [code]Classpath[/code] where it says Variable Name, and type SET [code]CLASSPATH=C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin;%CLASSPATH%;.[/code] Where it says Variable Value, Now Click Ok. Click the Same New button again Now for variable name we are putting [code] path [/code] And for Variable value we are putting [code] C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin;C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_06\bin [/code] [NOTE: In order for this to work you must have installed the latest version of JDK]
